\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus swallowed hard on seeing the System message about his Mana Control skill. Apparently the better you were at something in the System, the harder you got pushed to excel. Now he could only hope he could rise to the challenge. He concentrated, focusing his entire attention on the task at hand and shutting away everything else. The mana density in the room with him was skyrocketing, increasing an order of magnitude more quickly than it had in previous evaluations. It took everything he had learned, everything he had accomplished so far, to keep up with purifying, circulating and condensing the mana into his core. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Within what felt like mere minutes he was at the limit of what his existing pathways could handle and he felt them starting to break down. He needed better methods and more robust pathways if he was going to keep up. He needed another breakthrough in his understanding of mana, he needed something more than what he had been taught. He shut out the pain as he fell behind and the impure mana grated against his pathways and strained his core. Pain, after all, had been a constant companion of his for decades. It was practically an old friend.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mentally, he stepped back. Expanding his mana senses to see the whole picture of how he was handling the mana around him. He slowed his breathing, buying himself more time to find a solution before his current mana system would breakdown. Observe. Understand. Act. It was the most basic core principle he had ever relied on. Observe what is going on. Pay attention to every detail, no matter how minor. Keep observing until you see both the  patterns and the deviations from the pattern. Then you can understand. You can start to follow the causality, the cascade of effects resulting from both adhering to the pattern and deviating from it. Only after you understand can you act without adding chaos to the system. And you should never add unwanted chaos to an otherwise stable system.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He focused intently, studying the flow of mana and seeing the flaws, even ignoring the System notifications he felt accumulating. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 [The mana flow was slowing down, backing up. The unmoving mana that made up his core was bogging the whole system down, stealing the momentum of the mana flow. But how to fix that when it took time to compress the incoming mana into the core itself.]}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  He considered the problem for just a few moments before inspiration hit him. He reached into the mana at his core, and twisted, turning the mana. He focused and pictured a stick stirring the mana until it started moving. The he pushed it rotate faster, in a tighter circle before slightly altering the pathways into and out of his core. Now the faster moving, more dense mana coming into his system would maintain the rotation perpetually and the mana exiting would exit with the force of the rotation speeding it along. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Instantly the pain and pressure on his internal mana pathways began to ease, even as he continued to watch it closely and observe the effects of the change. To his surprise, the denser the mana around him became, the faster the entire system moved, fueled by increased incoming energy. Even more interesting was the fact that the mana rotating in his core was acting like a centrifuge, separating even more of affinities and impurities from the incoming mana and siphoning those unwanted parts into the outflow. More and more mana of ever greater purity and higher density was being pulled into his core this way. In fact, he felt himself nearing the threshold of a second compression. It just needed a little push and\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Abruptly the mana in the deepest part of his core collapsed inward like dying star and the rush of mana to fill the void thus created almost disrupted his entire flow. Gritting his teeth tightly, he pushed through the pain, once more reaching into his core and pushing the mana into motion, stabilizing and accelerating the rotation once again. It was an intensely unpleasant process as mana that }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 [hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t been purified enough rushed into his core to fill the void and only as he finally got it back up to speed and expelling unwanted affinities did the pain finally start to lessen.]}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  When his core fully stabilized at it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s new level of compression the pain vanished and he began to breath easier, relaxing. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Finally he turned to his accumulated System messages, scrolling through the list on his screen to the bottom and most important notifications. And there were a lot of them}
